This article discusses an executive order signed by President Biden that aims to address the climate crisis and put the United States at the forefront of global climate action. The order emphasizes the need for domestic and international efforts to tackle climate change and make the world more sustainable. It establishes policies and strategies to integrate climate considerations into foreign policy, national security, and government-wide approaches. The order also prioritizes clean energy, vehicle procurement, renewable energy, and fossil fuel subsidies. It emphasizes the importance of environmental justice, economic opportunity, and revitalization of communities affected by pollution and climate change. The order establishes interagency working groups, advisory councils, and reporting mechanisms to ensure the implementation and monitoring of these policies.